The paper proposes a novel approach to address two common issues in unsupervised GAN training, which are related to learning representations and memorization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) since the proposed approach is evaluated on image datasets. The paper also involves the use of memory networks, which are a type of neural network architecture, indicating a possible fit with cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques to evaluate the model, suggesting a possible fit with cs.CL (Computation and Language).
